The paper deals with a regression optimization problem with hierarchical interactions between variables, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a new algorithm to solve this problem and compares it with state-of-the-art methods. The paper also conducts experiments on both synthetic and real data. Based on this information, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
